n Leigh]] and [[Marisa Carroll]])\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.eharlequin.com/author.html?authorid=90 Joan Hohl's Webpage] in Harlequin Enterprises Ltd\n* [http://www.fantasticfiction.co.uk/h/joan-hohl Joan Hohl's Webpage] and [http://www.fantasticfiction.co.uk/l/amii-lorin Amii Lorin's Webpage] in Fantastic Fiction's Website\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hohl, Joan}}\n[[Category:1935 births]]\n[[Category:2017 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century American novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American novelists]]\n[[Category:20th-century American women writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women writers]]\n[[Category:American romantic fiction writers]]\n[[Category:American women novelists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\n| image =  \n| name = Joan Hohl\n| caption =\n| pseudonym = Paula Roberts, Amii Lorin, Joan Hohl\n| birth_date = {{Birth date|1935|6|13|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = United States\n| death_date = {{Death date and age|2017|06|16|1935|6|13|mf=y}}\n| death_place =\n| occupation = Novelist\n| nationality = American\n| period = 1980-present\n| genre = [[Romance novel|Romance]]\n| subject =\n| movement =\n| influences =\n| influenced =\n| signature =\n| awards = [[RITA Award]]\n| website =\n}}\n'''Joan Hohl''' (June 13, 1935 \u2013 June 16, 2017) was an American writer of over 60 [[romance novel]]s starting in 1980.<ref name=\"obit\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.tributearchive.com/obituaries/2776748/Joan-M-Hohl |title=Joan M. Hohl Obituary |website=www.tributearchive.com |language=en |access-date=2019-10-14}}</ref> She signed her novels as '''Paula Roberts''' and '''Amii Lorin'''.<ref name=\"obit\"/> She was a recipient of the [[RITA Award]].\n\n==Biography==\nJoan Hohl was born in the United States, June 13, 1935. She worked at several jobs, some sales clerking, but primarily factory work.\n\nAt 40, she began writing, and three years later